      <div class="msgContentFrame">I don't know if this is the best way but <br /> <br />I have found that spamming Heavy Thrust in parties is the best (as oppossed to light thrust when solo), especially on heavy defense mobs, because you get a proc for damage, and a proc for the debuff.  <br /> <br />So on a crab, it would look something like:  <br />You gain 30 Polearm skill points <br />You gain 110 Polearm skill points <br /> <br />The 110 being from the debuff <br /> <br />Besides that, I keep Speed Surge up, I use feint every single time I can, and my WS of choice is Moonrise and Leg Sweep as a secondary WS. <br /> <br />Speed surge as oppossed to Life Surge because Speed surge increases my DPS, and I don't really care if my allies get their attacks evaded. Moonrise as oppossed to anything else because I have found that it debuffs the enemy 100% on hit. If it hits, it WILL debuff the enemy, which means better SP gains than procs with %. And leg sweep because hey, sh*t happens, sometimes you need a stun. <br /> <br />I will keep Comrade in Arms up if I have the extra stamina, and I have extra SP. It's not a big deal, and it's not a priority, but it helps. <br /> <br />One thing I do is- never moonrise unless you have over 1500TP. That way you can do Moonrise (Miss) -&gt; Feint -&gt; Attack (Miss) -&gt; Feint. If you keep missing after that, that sucks, but it doesn't happen often. <br /> <br />Oh. And use ferocity with Feint. </div>
