      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Meowshi wrote:</div><div class="orig">So on a crab, it would look something like:  <br />You gain 30 Polearm skill points <br />You gain 110 Polearm skill points <br /> <br />The 110 being from the debuff</div></div> <br /> <br />No, the 30 is debuff and 110 is for the hit.  <br /> <br />After grinding 2.75 hours at Black Eft, I noticed that if you alternate between skills you get a much better chance of getting SP. Don't just Thrust -&gt; Feint -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Feint -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Feint, throw in different skill attack in between. What I do is Life Surge -&gt; Invigorate -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Ferocity -&gt; Trammel/Heavy Trammel -&gt; Thrust/Feint -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Moonrise/Skewer II -&gt; Thrust/Feint -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Moonrise/Skewer II (The other one that you didnt use earlier), most likely it's dead by now. About 75% of the kills I get 500 full SP, the rest randomly from 0-300. Life Surge helps in a big party, debuff Eva is good.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1807831.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
