      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Omena wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Khornette wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />I would call yours BS as well, because my Skewer II that doesn't debuff gain twice the SP compare to Heavy Trammel/Moonrise that DOES debuff. Getting 284 SP from a Skewer II proc on a Black Eft vs getting 55 SP and 150 SP from a Heavy Trammel. Mind you, the Black Eft has way more DEF than Stoneshell, which is several ranks higher than Thickshell/Island Crab, and I was in a party of 13-15 people.</div></div> <br />First of all, Skewer II does more damage than Trammel, so it's going to get you more SP from the damage component. Secondly, you're presenting anecdotal evidence based on eye balling rather than parsing or even reasoning as fact. This is how all those stupid rumours we had floating around in FFXI for years get started. Finally, SP gains are still random to some extent and last time I did a skill up PT my Heavy procs could add anything between 40 and 120 points without the party size or mobs changing. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov  7th 2010  6:03pm by Omena </span></i></div></div> <br /> <br />First of all, didn't that just prove that the more SP proc was the damage and not the debuff? Secondly, you can't even be sure which part of the 2 SP gain was for debuff and for damage hit, how do you prove that? Damage hit -&gt; SP also get SP bonus from the party size too, unless your normal attack on the Thickshell gives 1 SP, then that 30 SP gain maybe reasonably the damage did by Trammel. As far as I can recall, crap normal attack on Thickshell give somewhere from 20-30 SP as well unless that Thickshell is actually GREEN to you ALONE. Finally, SP gains are still random to some extent, there is actually no proof against or for any theory right now.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1807831.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
